# History: wave-based-bulk-issue-triage

## v1.2.0 — 2026-04-12

**Amendment**: Add issue classification phase, wave-by-fix-type grouping, agent plan-mode
avoidance pattern, and JIT crash identification heuristic.

### Changes from v1.1.0

- Bumped version to 1.2.0, updated date to 2026-04-12
- Updated description to mention pre-fix classification phase
- **When to Use**: Added item 6 — large backlogs (20+ issues) requiring classification first
- **Phase 0 (NEW)**: Issue classification using 3 parallel Explore agents (~22 issues each)
  - Explore (not Haiku) required — classification requires judgment, not just mechanics
  - Classification levels: LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH / N/A with rationale
  - Pre-classification exclusions: skip epic, blocked, and audit summary issues
- **Phase 1 (REFINED)**: Wave grouping by fix type (A: docs → B: config → C: code → D: tests)
  - Ordering minimizes CI queue time: Wave A PRs often merge before Wave D starts
  - MEDIUM/HIGH issues excluded from waves, handled individually
- **Phase 2 (AMENDED)**: Added `model="haiku"` to Task calls and imperative prompt form
  - Root cause of plan-mode stalling: Sonnet agents with isolation=worktree over-plan
  - Fix: Haiku model + `Run:` command form + `IMPORTANT: DO NOT PLAN. EXECUTE IMMEDIATELY.`
- **Prompt Template**: Rewritten in imperative `Run:` form; explanation of why descriptive
  phrasing triggers planning behavior
- **Results**: New section for 2026-04-11 ProjectOdyssey session (66 classified, 28 fixed,
  28 PRs)
- **CI JIT Crash Heuristic (NEW)**: If all jobs fail with same `execution crashed` in
  `libKGENCompilerRTShared.so`, it is a JIT flake — re-run CI, do not investigate code
- **Failed Attempts**: Added two new rows for plan-mode stalling (descriptive prompts,
  "complete all steps" text)
- **Verified On**: Added ProjectOdyssey entry

### Verification

- verified-local: 66 issues classified, 28 fixed, 28 PRs created on
  HomericIntelligence/ProjectOdyssey (2026-04-11); CI running

---

## v1.1.0 — 2026-04-06

**Amendment**: Add myrmidon swarm pattern for bulk `gh issue create` operations.

### Changes from v1.0.0
- Bumped version to 1.1.0, updated date to 2026-04-06
- Added `verification: verified-local` to frontmatter (was missing)
- Added `history` frontmatter field pointing to this file
- Extended description to cover bulk gh issue create via myrmidon swarm
- **When to Use**: Added item 5 — filing 10+ GitHub issues from an audit or walkthrough report
- **Results**: New section "Myrmidon Swarm Pattern for Bulk Issue Filing" covering:
  - Plain Agent calls (not Task isolation:worktree) for pure gh issue create
  - Haiku model tier for fully-specified commands requiring no design decisions
  - Wave limit: ≤5 agents per wave to prevent API rate limiting
  - No worktrees needed when no repository files are modified
  - Body-file pattern for issue bodies containing single quotes or apostrophes
  - Verified: 11 issues in ~30s (HomericIntelligence/Odysseus #99-#109)
- **Failed Attempts**: Added body quoting gotcha — single-quoted strings break on embedded apostrophes; use `--body-file` instead
- **Verified On**: Added HomericIntelligence/Odysseus entry

### Verification
- verified-local: 11 issues filed on HomericIntelligence/Odysseus (#99-109) on 2026-04-06

---

## v1.0.0 — 2026-02-22 (snapshot)

**Original skill** — Wave-based bulk issue triage using `Task(isolation="worktree")`.

### Summary
- Verified on ProjectScylla: 8 PRs created (Wave 6+7), 23 new tests, ~2 min per wave
- Pattern: Group issues by complexity → Wave A (simple) then Wave B (test additions)
- Key innovation: `Task(isolation="worktree")` — zero manual worktree management
- Issues resolved: #920, #930, #959, #985, #986, #987, #898, #1042
- PRs created: #1051–#1059

### Frontmatter at v1.0.0
```yaml
name: wave-based-bulk-issue-triage
description: "Fix 5+ independent GitHub issues in parallel waves using Task isolation:worktree. No manual worktree setup — Claude Code auto-manages isolation."
category: architecture
date: 2026-02-22
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
